*'''Expert Tactician''': Nadeem was skilled at formulating plans, going to [[Tammy Hattley]] with an idea of using [[Wilson Fisk]] for intel. This allowed them to catch many criminals like the [[Albanian Syndicate]] and [[Mother Teresa]]. However, Fisk used this to exploit everyone in the [[FBI]] and make them work for him. When Nadeem found this out, he originally allowed himself to be coerced in order to save his family, but he eventually joined [[Daredevil]]'s side and worked to stop Fisk. Knowing he would probably die due to his actions, Nadeem recorded a dying declaration, knowing it would be admissible in court as dying declarations are seen as something that the victim would not lie about. This was the driving force in not only putting Kingpin in jail, but also stopping Daredevil from killing Fisk.
*'''Expert Investigator''': As an [[FBI]] agent, Nadeem was very good with his investigating skills, being able to trail [[Matt Murdock]] and find his home where he saw his clothes on the ground. When teaming up with Daredevil, Nadeem broke into [[Benjamin Poindexter's Apartment]] and looked through the place. He was able to find many pieces of evidence like audio recordings from a young [[Benjamin Poindexter|Poindexter]]. He also attempted to get information from [[Karen Page]] and [[Foggy Nelson]].
*'''Expert Combatant''': Nadeem could protect himself well. While being chased, Nadeem went toe-to-tie with one of his assailants and was able to beat him. he also knocked out [[Foggy Nelson]] with one punch.
*'''Expert Marksman''': As an [[FBI]] agent, Nadeem knew how to carry a gun and used it in his work. When men broke into [[Nadeem Residence]], he armed himself with his gun and protected his family, shooting many enemies. He was also engaged in a shootout with [[Benjamin Poindexter]] as the two shot each other through an alley. He also used his gun while being chased and with [[Matt Murdock]]'s guidance, was able to shoot enemies through the walls of his van.
*'''Bilingualism''': Nadeem was fluent in his native Hindi, as well as English.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
*'''{{WPS|Glock 17}}''': Nadeem carried this handgun as his standard sidearm. He carried it when he was deployed to [[Arrest of the Albanian Syndicate|arrest]] the [[Albanian Syndicate]] with the information provided by [[Wilson Fisk]]; to [[Raid on Matt Murdock's Apartment|raid]] [[Matt Murdock]]'s [[Matt Murdock's Apartment|apartment]], as Fisk had accused him of being a facilitator in his crimes; and when he searched for the [[Benjamin Poindexter|man responsible]] for [[Attack on the New York Bulletin Building|attacking]] the [[New York Bulletin Building]] dressed as [[Daredevil]]. He surrendered the gun to [[Tammy Hattley]] along with his badge when he informed her of Fisk's conspiracy, though Hattley used the gun to [[Murder of Winn|kill]] [[Winn]] instead and have leverage against him. Nadeem was given another service gun that he carried while he [[Search for Daredevil|searched]] for [[Daredevil]] in the [[Clinton Church]], and also in the attacks by Fisk's men that were [[Chase of Ray Nadeem|chasing him]], first in his house and then when he was being taken to the courthouse to testify against Fisk. Finally, he used the gun one last time to try to protect himself from [[Benjamin Poindexter]] when he was sent to [[Assassination of Ray Nadeem|kill]] him, but Poindexter was faster and killed him with a single shot to the head.

